Bleto] Ant. du Blet († 0. May 1526), a banker or merchant of Lycus, who was in close sympathy with the Reformers. In the spring of 1524 he accompanied Farel to visit Zwin li at Zurich. They were at Basle in t e middle of May (Herminjard 100, 101 ; LE2. 795), at Constanee early in June (Ep. 1454. 18), and du Blet had returned to France by the end of the mouth.
